  "instructions": [
    "heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large cataplana over medium-high heat.",
    "add the beef and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the onion, garlic, and caraway seeds to the pot and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "add the hoisin sauce, beef broth, tomato paste, and bay leaves to the pot.",
    "bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 2 1/2 hours.",
    "remove the bay leaves and season the stew with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "if using, stir in the apple cider vinegar.",
    "serve the stew hot, garnished with fresh parsley or dill, if desired."
